The 2006 Postal Accountability and Enhancement Act required the Postal Service to pre-fund future retiree health benefits, not pensions.
Background on the Postal ServiceThe Postal Service is a unique agency.
The health benefit requirementThe 2006 law also established a fund for Postal Service retiree health benefits.
But Jim Campbell, a private attorney and an expert on postal service laws, said the 2006 law also freed the Postal Service of a prior obligation to cover pension costs for military service its employees completed before joining the Postal Service.
The Facebook post suggests that if the Postal Service could get rid of the 2006 law, everything else would be fine.